31/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Four soldiers died on Sunday (August 30th) in a hand grenade attack that authorities blamed on members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK). It happened near the town of Semdinli, close to the Iraqi border in the southeast province of Hakkari. The soldiers were patrolling when Kurdish rebels hurled the grenade at their vehicle, authorities said. (Vatan, Cumhurriyet, Radikal - 31/08/09; AFP, Reuters - 30/08/09)
